\"She has now landed a triple Axel in three consecutive events to start the season, though Friday's was judged a quarter turn short and given a slightly negative grade of execution (-0.34).\", \"from\": 511, \"to\": 698, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 532, \"end\": 543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Axel_jump\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"triple Axel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Axel_jump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Axel_jump\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Glenn then stumbled out of the landing and put her hands on the ice on the back half of a triple flip-triple toe loop combination.\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 829, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"CUP OF CHINA:Broadcast Schedule  \\\"I have not felt my best since I have been here so I have been just really focused on the mental side and staying strong in that,\\\" Glenn said, according to the International Skating Union.\", \"from\": 831, \"to\": 1052, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1046, \"end\": 1051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999998840394, \"rank\": 1.1582098543365585e-10, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Glenn, 25, earned her first career Grand Prix win in France earlier this month.\", \"from\": 1054, \"to\": 1133, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1089, \"end\": 1099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ISU_Grand_Prix_of_Figure_Skating\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0172956269292187e-84, \"text\": \"Grand Prix\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ISU_Grand_Prix_of_Figure_Skating\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ISU_Grand_Prix_of_Figure_Skating\"}, {\"begin\": 1107, \"end\": 1113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6992130916077176, \"rank\": 0.41253618175541173, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She can become the fifth U.S. woman to win two Grand Prix events in one season after Michelle Kwan (1995, 1996, 1997, 1999), Sasha Cohen (2002, 2003), Alissa Czisny (2010) and Ashley Wagner (2012).\", \"from\": 1134, \"to\": 1331, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1219, \"end\": 1227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\", \"score\": 0.9999999717106225, \"rank\": 2.8024513691695745e-08, \"text\": \"Michelle\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\"}, {\"begin\": 1259, \"end\": 1270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sasha_Cohen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sasha Cohen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sasha_Cohen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sasha_Cohen\"}, {\"begin\": 1285, \"end\": 1298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alissa_Czisny\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alissa Czisny\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alissa_Czisny\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alissa_Czisny\"}, {\"begin\": 1310, \"end\": 1323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashley_Wagner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ashley Wagner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashley_Wagner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashley_Wagner\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The series debuted in 1995.\", \"from\": 1332, \"to\": 1359, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the Grand Prix Series, top skaters compete twice each over the six-event regular season in October and November, all scattered among different competitions.\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1520, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The top six per discipline over the regular season qualify for December's Grand Prix Final, the first event of the season to gather all of the world's top-ranked skaters.\", \"from\": 1522, \"to\": 1692, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Final is often a preview of the following March's world championships.\", \"from\": 1693, \"to\": 1767, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Glenn will qualify for her first Grand Prix Final if she places in the top three at Cup of China and could also make it by finishing lower depending on how other skaters finish.\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1946, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1860, \"end\": 1865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9644338942344346, \"rank\": 0.03487287931124607, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Cup of China short program was very close with the top five separated by 1.78 points.\", \"from\": 1947, \"to\": 2036, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1958, \"end\": 1963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9644338942344346, \"rank\": 0.03487287931124607, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Also at Cup of China, two-time world medalists Charl\\u00e8ne Guignard and Marco Fabbri of Italy lead after the rhythm dance and are in position to clinch a spot in the Final.\", \"from\": 2038, \"to\": 2207, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2053, \"end\": 2058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9644338942344346, \"rank\": 0.03487287931124607, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"